            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Hd1e108">Rubrica 1</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De bono et malo</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e114">
      <!--56.xml-->
               <pb ed="#V" n="15-r"/>
               <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>SEcundus liber prime partis
      <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>tractat de bono et honesto vir
      <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>tutibus et contrariis sub his ti
      <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>tulis sequentibus. 
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e132">
               <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>
      ¶ De bono et ma
      <lb ed="#V" n="6" break="no"/>lo. Rubrica prima.
      
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e139">
               <lb ed="#V" n="7"/> <ref>IOb hysto. cap. 28.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e143">Recedem a
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>malo est intelligentia </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e150">
               <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>
             ¶ <ref> In genesi. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e154">Sensus et cogita
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>tino humani cordis in malum pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="11" break="no"/>na sunt ab adolescentia sua.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e162">
               <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>
            ¶ <ref>Amos propheta. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e166">Odite malum et diligi
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>te bonum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e172">
               <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>
            ¶ <ref>Esaias propheta. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e176">Uhe qui dicitis malum
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>bonum et bonum malum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e182">
               <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>
            ¶ <ref>Plato in menone.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e186">Non vult mala quis
        <lb ed="#V" n="17" break="no"/>piam. Nullus vult mala. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e192">
               <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>
            ¶ <ref>Aristotelis ethincorum libro i. c. i. in princi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e196">Omnis ars
        <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>et omnis doctrina similiter autem et actus: et electio
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>bonum quoddam appetere videtur. Ideo bene an
        <lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>nunciauerunt bonum quod omnia appetunt. Multis
        <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>contingunt detrimenta ex bonis: iam enim qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="23" break="no"/>dam perierunt propter diuitias: alii veo propter
        <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>fortitudinem. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e213"> /
       <ref>c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e215">Omnis cognitio et electio
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>bonum aliquod desiderat. Bonum et felicitatem
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>non irronnabiliter videntur ex his que huius vi
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>te sunt ex istimare. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e226"> /
       <ref>Libro. 2 c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e228">Malum
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>infiniti est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e234"> /
     <ref>li. 4. c. 4.</ref>  <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e236"> Malum seipsum destruit </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e240">
               <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>
               / <ref>Libro. 7. c. 15. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e244" source="http://scta.info/resource/ArNeTH-d1e150-d1e1522@30-34">Malo bonum contrarium
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e250"> /
       <ref>Libro. 9. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e252">Unusquisque sibipsi vult
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>bona. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e258"> /
               <ref>Li. 10. et fi. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e260" source="http://scta.info/resource/ArNeTH-d1e593-d1e232@152-157">Et in prauis est ali
               <lb ed="#V" n="32" break="no"/>quod naturale bonum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e266"> /
       <ref>Idem magnorum mo
        <lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>ralium li. i. c. i.</ref> <!--ref but no quote-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e275"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e277"> Nulla neque scientia neque potem <!--quote but no ref-->
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>tia est causa mali. In vno quoque entium bonum
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>aut optimum est quod propter sui naturam est appe
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>tibile: aut quo alia participantia bona sunt.
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>Bonorum hic quidem inanima: puta virtus: hic ant
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>in corpore: puta sanitas et pulchritudo: alia
        <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>vero exterius diuitie principatus honor vel si
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>quid aliud talium. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e296"> /
       <ref>Idem rheto. li. i. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e298">Bo
        <lb ed="#V" n="41" break="no"/>num est quodcumque sui gratia est eligibile: et cu
        <lb ed="#V" n="42" break="no"/>ius gratia aliud eligimus: et quod omnia appetunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e306">
               <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>
            <ref>/ c. 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e310">Bonum dicimus quod ipsum sui gratia
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>et non alterius eligibile est: et quod omnia appetunt. <!--56.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>Bonum est aut delectabile aut quod secundum se eligi
        <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>bile. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e324"> /
       <ref>Li. 2 c. 16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e326">Plura eorum que fiunt ma
        <lb ed="#V" n="47" break="no"/>la sunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e332"> /
       <ref>Idem polliticorum libro i. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e334">Eius quod
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>videtur bonigratia omnia operantur omnes. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e340"> /
       <ref>ca. 3</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e342">Quod efficitur a melioribus: melius opus est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e349">
               <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e353">/ Idem topicorum. Omnia appetunt bonum </quote> <!--no reference-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e357"> /
      <ref>Li.
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e359"> Bonum est malo contrarium. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e365">
               <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>
               ¶ <ref>Tullius retho. artis noue li. 2. c. 6.</ref> <!--but no quotes-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e373"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e375"> Omnium <!--quote with no ref-->
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>malorum stultitia est mater atque materies. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e381">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>
              <ref>/ Idem tusculanarum quodonum li. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e385">Insipientia nul
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>lum maius malum est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e391"> /
      <ref>Li. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e393"> Natura omnes
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>ea que bona videntur sequuntur fugiuntque con
        <lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>traria. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e402"> /
      <ref>Idem de fine bonorum et malorum: libro 5
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>et fi.</ref> <!--ref but no quote-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e410"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e412"> Consitendum est id esse summum bonum
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>quod certe vniuersum sua sponte ipsum expe
        <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>ti et propter se necesse est. </quote> <!--quote but no ref-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e420"> /
      <ref>Idem paradoxorum
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>distinctione. i.</ref> <!--ref but no quote-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e428"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e430">Quod rectum et honestum et cum
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>virtute est id solum oppinor bonum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e436"> /
      <ref>Idem
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>de legibus li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e438">Quod laudabile bonum est in
        <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>se habet quod laudetur necesse est: ipsum enim
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>bonum non est opinionibus sed natura. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e448">
               <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>
            ¶ <ref>Ouidius de arte amandi li. 3. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e452">Pluraque
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>sunt semper deteriora bonis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e459"> /
      <ref>Idem de tristi
        <lb ed="#V" n="68" break="no"/>bus li. 2 epistola vnica.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e461"> Nil prodest quod non lede
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>re possit idem. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e469">
               <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>
            ¶ <ref>Seneca epistolarum ad lucillum li. 8. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e473">Bonum
        <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>omne diuinum est.</quote> / <ref>Li. 15. c. i.</ref> <quote>Sapientia perfe
        <lb ed="#V" n="72" break="no"/>ctum bonum est mentis humane. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e481"> /
      <ref>Li. 20. et fi.
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e483">Bonum est quod ad se impetum animi secundum
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>naturam mouet. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e491"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e493"> Idem de consolatione ad pau
        <lb ed="#V" n="75" break="no"/>linum. Non sentire mala sua non est hominus: et non
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>ferre non est viri. </quote> <!--no reference-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e501"> /
       <ref>Idem de naturalibus quod
        <lb ed="#V" n="77" break="no"/>nibus li. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e503">Nullum malum si est effugio est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e509">
               <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>
            ¶ <ref>Cecilius firmianus de beata vita lib. 3.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e513">Bonorum matura in arduo posita est: malorum
        <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>in precipitio. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e522"> /
       <ref>Li. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e524">Est pene supra humma
        <lb ed="#V" n="81" break="no"/>num modum ne in cognitionem quidem admittere
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>quod fit vel factum malum vel improbum dictum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e532">
               <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>
            <ref>/ Li. 7. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e536">Deus non excludit malum vt ratio
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>virtutis constare posset. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e542">
               <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>
            ¶ <ref>Augustinus in epig. prosperi. 75. estp.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e546">Non suf
        <lb ed="#V" n="86" break="no"/>ficit abstinere a malo nisi fiat quod bonum
        <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>est. Nulla substantia iniquitas est: et peccatu
        <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>non est natura: sed vitiu nature appetentis
        <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>id quod non est sui ordinis. <!--57.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="15-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e565">
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
            ¶ <ref>Boetius de consola. li. 3. c. 19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e569">Omnium exi
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>petendorum summa cardo atque causa est bonum: quod
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>enim neque re neque similitudine vllum in se retinet
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>bonum: id expeti nullo modo potest. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e579"> /
       <ref>Li. 4. c. 3</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="5"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e581">Omnes homines boni ac pariter mali idiscreta in
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>tentione ad bonum peruenire nituntur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e589"> /
      <ref>c. 7.</ref> Bo
        <lb ed="#V" n="7" break="no"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e591">num est omne quod iustum est: contraque quod iniustum
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>est malum esse liquet. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e600"> /
      <ref>c. 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e602">Et si nobis fata
        <lb ed="#V" n="9" break="no"/>lem ordinem minime considerare valentibus confu
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>sa omnia conturbataque videantur: nihilominus tantum
        <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>suus modus ad bonum dirigens cuncta dispo
        <lb ed="#V" n="12" break="no"/>nit. Nihil est quod mali causa ne etiam ab ipsis quidem
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>improbis fiat: quos bonum querentes prauus
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>error auertit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e619"> /
       <ref>Idem topicorum li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e621">Mali no
        <lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>titia deesse non potest bono: virtus enim se
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>diligit: aspernaturque contraria: ne vitare vi
        <lb ed="#V" n="17" break="no"/>tium nisi cognitum queat. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e631"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e633"> Idem de hebdoma <!--no reference-->
        <lb ed="#V" n="18" break="no"/>dibus. Omnium rerum ipsum esse bonum est. Bo
        <lb ed="#V" n="19" break="no"/>num esse essentia. Iustum vero esse actum respicit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>Bona omnia sunt etiam non iusta. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e643">
               <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>
            ¶ <ref>Gualterius de castellione li. 3 circa med.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="22"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e647">Omnia cum quodam veniunt incommoda fructu. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-d1e653">
               <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>
            ¶ <ref>Auctor libelli de moribus medicorum. ca. i.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="24"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d10983-Qd1e657">Omnia scire decet: cuncta patrare nocet.
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>Scire malum quod nitet idem res conueniens est
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>Scire bonum discat quilibet id quod amat.
      </quote>
            </p>
